CLARIFICATION AND SPECIAL EXCEPTION FOR NMAP DISTRIBUTION
================================================================================

This software is licensed under GPL v3 or later to retain maximum rights
for IntegSec while ensuring compatibility with open source requirements.

SPECIAL EXCEPTION FOR NMAP:
When distributed as part of the official Nmap distribution or the Nmap
Scripting Engine library, this script may also be used under:
  - The Nmap Public Source License (NPSL), OR
  - The Nmap license as specified at https://nmap.org/book/man-legal.html

This exception allows the script to be distributed with Nmap while
maintaining GPL v3+ for standalone distribution.

CLARIFICATION:
- When distributed WITH Nmap: Either GPL v3+, NPSL, or Nmap license applies
- When distributed SEPARATELY from Nmap: GPL v3 or later applies
- IntegSec retains all copyright and intellectual property rights
- This script may be freely used, modified, and distributed under the
  terms specified above

================================================================================
WHY GPL v3+?
================================================================================

IntegSec has chosen GPL v3 or later because it:
1. Ensures the software remains free and open source
2. Requires derivatives to also be open source (copyleft protection)
3. Retains IntegSec's copyright and attribution rights
4. Allows commercial use with proper attribution
5. Is compatible with Nmap's licensing requirements through the special exception
6. Protects against patent claims
7. Ensures source code availability for all users

This maximizes IntegSec's rights while keeping the software publicly available
and free for the community.

